sequenceDiagram
    participant WORKLOAD as Workload (Pod)
    participant AGENT as SPIRE Agent\n(DaemonSet on node)
    participant SERVER as SPIRE Server\n(control plane)
    participant PEER as Peer Service\n(another workload)

    Note over WORKLOAD,SERVER: Phase 1 — Node Attestation (once per node)

    AGENT->>SERVER: Node attestation request\n(AWS IID / K8s SAT / TPM)
    SERVER->>SERVER: Verify node identity\nagainst attestation plugin
    SERVER-->>AGENT: Node SVID issued\n(X.509 cert for this node)

    Note over WORKLOAD,SERVER: Phase 2 — Workload Attestation (per pod)

    WORKLOAD->>AGENT: RequestX509SVID()\n(via Unix domain socket\n/run/spire/sockets/agent.sock)
    AGENT->>AGENT: Inspect calling process:\n• Kubernetes SA annotations\n• Pod labels and namespace\n• Container image digest
    AGENT->>SERVER: Workload attestation request\n{namespace, serviceAccount, podLabels}
    SERVER->>SERVER: Match against registration entries:\nspiffe://cluster.local/ns/payments/sa/payments-api
    SERVER-->>AGENT: X.509 SVID issued\n(short-lived: 1 hour default)\nSAN = SPIFFE ID
    AGENT-->>WORKLOAD: X.509 SVID + trust bundle\nDelivered via UNIX socket\n(no secret, no file mount needed)

    Note over WORKLOAD,PEER: Phase 3 — mTLS between services

    WORKLOAD->>PEER: TLS ClientHello\n(presents X.509 SVID)
    PEER->>PEER: Verify SVID against\nSPIFFE trust bundle
    PEER->>WORKLOAD: TLS ServerHello\n(presents own X.509 SVID)
    WORKLOAD->>WORKLOAD: Verify peer SVID\nCheck SPIFFE ID is in allowlist:\nspiffe://cluster.local/ns/orders/sa/orders-api
    WORKLOAD-->>PEER: mTLS channel established\nMutual authentication complete

    Note over AGENT,SERVER: Continuous — SVID rotation

    AGENT->>SERVER: Re-attestation before SVID expiry\n(at 50% of TTL by default)
    SERVER-->>AGENT: New SVID issued\nOld SVID still valid until expiry
    AGENT-->>WORKLOAD: New SVID pushed via socket\nZero downtime rotation
